Galaxy Backbone Limited is seeking a tripartite partnership with the Ministry of Budget and National Planning and the Bureau for Public Procurement (BPP) to strengthen effective delivery of federal government’s e-governance and digital economy mandate. The possible areas of collaboration and partnership were the crux of deliberations when the top management of Galaxy Backbone led by its managing director, Prof. Muhammad Bello Abubakar, paid a courtesy visit on the minister of State for Budget and National Planning, Prince Clem Ikanade Agba in his office in Abuja. Abubakar pointed out Galaxy Backbone Limited is an Information and Communications Technology (ICT) services provider, wholly owned by the Federal Government of Nigeria, under the direct supervision of the Ministry of Communications and Digital Economy to provide IP network support to ministries, departments and agencies (MDAs). “Galaxy Backbone has the mandate to generate revenue for government and to operate under the leadership of Bureau for Public Procurement (BPP) Act. “We are supposed to champion the e-governance policy of the federal government and the digital economy under the leadership of Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami,” he said In his response, Agba, revealed the ministry’s readiness to partner with the organization in fulfilling government’s e-government mandate, even as he urged MDAs of government as well as the other arms of the federal government and individuals to patronize Galaxy Backbone.